column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Partly cloudy- high winds- and heavy rain on 7/12/1987.
Sunny- partly cloudy- slight algae bloom- and water still had some chop after yesterday's high west winds.
Sunny- light to moderate chop- water has slight olive drab tinge.
Partly cloudy- calm- water green to clear.
Cloudy- slight chop- first day in 5 without rain.
Sunny- mild- but very windy- moderate to heavy chop on water- rained earlier today.
Sunny- mild- slight to moderate chop- wind increasing- rain yesterday.
Sunny- hot- mod. chop- power boats-- greater than turbulence.
Clear/sunny- hot- slight chop- rain 48 hours ago- more boats than normal.
Partly sunny- some chop- boats- hot and muggy.
Partly cloudy- hot- light to mod. chop- limited boating.
Sunny- hot- some wind- moderate chop on water.
Sunny- windy- warm- mod. chop on water.
Sunny- mild- light chop on water.
Sunny- cool- quite windy- no cloudy- choppy.
Sunny- breezy- cool- light to moderate chop.
Slightly overcast- sunny- fall colors beautiful- light chop- last reading.
Bright. sun- slight chop- reading deeper than norm.- weather cool- Department of Natural Resources shocked lake recently for fish survey.
Sunny- warm but water is cold- many tent caterpillars and flies.
Less tent caterpillars + flies- sunny- warm W wind- chop on water.
More people on lake than most July 4ths- resident loons have 2 chicks.
Partly cloudy- sunny- brisk wind- chop on water- slight olive color to water.
Hazy blue sky- mod.-heavy chop on water- over 1 in. rain past 3 days.
Clear- brisk wind- some fall colors- Canadian geese earlier today- last reading.
Slight overcast- water stirred up by winds and July 4th.
Overcast- haze- rainy past 5 days + AM- reading during cloud break.
Clear- sunny- hot- windy- chop- finally air and water warm enough to swim.
Sunny- warm- windy- chop- cool in AM.
Sunny- fairly calm- has been overcast- windy- or rainy for past week.
Very sunny- clear- fairly calm- no boat wakes.
Sunny- slight. Haze- fog earlier- wind- moderate chop.
Sun bright- 17 large gaggles of Canadian geese w/in 4 hours.
Bright sun- very windy- rainy past 3 days with heavy chop- last reading.
Storm damage (about 5/28) - loons. Water level: Up 3"
Weather has been erratic: frequently overcast and cold.
Overcast- rainy past 4 days- today is clear and windy- loons- heron- bald eagles- and mink sighted.
Fishing poor- only 1/2 of Wisconsin's lakes have average population of walleyes- pH: above 8.0.
Leaves starting to turn (4-6 weeks early)- fishing poor- 70 F- cool during night- 54 F at 9:00 AM.
Good weather the past 4 days- 78 F- clear- undersized fish caught and released- very few legal fish- 2 eagles sighted.
Unidentified waterfowl on lake (red necked grebe with winter coloration).
Proposed change of no wake hours from 4-11 to 7-10 has many upset.
Weather has been more than a minor aesthetic problem most of the summer.
Yesterday and today were the only days in July so far for swimming.  Blue herons seen over on the lake.  Fishing is poor- fish are all very small.
Clearest day I've had to take a reading- totally sunny at the time of measurement.  Surface had a light chop from the wind- but nicest "summer" day this year.
Partly sunny- hazy. Very windy and surface is choppy.
Best weather all summer but its still cool.  Lots of boats but no one is swimming- water is too cold.
Hot- humid- overcast with occasional rain.
Intermittent sun and overcast- hail earlier in day- squall arrived as I left lake.
Overcast- beach crowded- more boats than normal- poor fishing this year.
Much sunshine- water warmer + day clearer than on any previous reading days this year.
Partly cloudy- just enough wind for sailing.
Too cool for swimming- weather alternated sunny/cloudy/ and overcast all day long.
I will leave Boot Lake for winter by the end of September  I expect to return June 1984.

This is the greatest depth I have measured in 8 years of testing and it should be deeper- as I could still see the disk when I came to the end of my 28.5' secchi rope.  It would have been visible to at least 30'.  I will use a longer rope.
Confirms previous reading of unused clarity.  Disc hit bottom in West Basin reading only.  That basin has deeper hole- but I couldn't find it today.
Very hot (94 degrees) + windy.  Chop on surface interfered with seeing disc as deep as if surface were calmer.
Weather moderating after several very hot days (90+) .  Readings becoming nearer to those of previous years.  Still somewhat deeper.
Public perception due to overcast cool weather.
Windy- hazy- heavy chop on water.  Has been overcast- rainy- windy for about 10 days.  Some days cold- others very hot.
This is an unusual year- starting out with greatest depth I have ever measured- decreasing in depth each reading until it is less than 3'-more than my 8 year shallowest reading.
Sun behind clouds from 2:00-3:30.  Delaying reading about 1.5 hours.  Deeper reading than previous one for 1st time this year.
Continues increase begun 7/24.  I will be unable to take reading next 2 weeks.
Sunny- warm.  Had 2 days of rain- heavy first day- this week.
Hot (84 degrees) and sunny.  Front came through at 10 pm followed by 10 minutes of 55 mph winds- than calm again.
Cool-65 degrees.  Had 2 severe wind storms (up to 50-55 mph for brief period) with some rain during past week.
Shallowest readings of year.  Some "balls" of algae floating in water- particularly in West Basin.
Floating algae gone.  Windy and cool- but beautiful fall day.
Cold- windy- overcast.  Some readings over 30' this year-please send longer rope.  Going to winter home.
Both air temperature and water temperature unseasonably high for past week.
Rain earlier in day.  Somewhat cloudy + cooler.
Best conditions for secchi this year.  Color selections don't seem to fit.  I would call it clear/green- almost like old window glass.
Very windy-chop severe enough to affect reading (lower the number of feet disc could be seen).
Conditions nearly ideal for good secchi reading-clear- calm- warm.
Hot + windy.  Very unusual for West Basin reading to be greater than that for East Basin.
Beautiful today following week of rain and/or high wind.
Beautiful day!  Fairly heavy boat traffic- some wind.
Public perception due to unseasonally cold and overcast skies.  Water quality good but cold-temperature about 47 degrees at 1:30 P.M.
Sorry to be so late with first reading but we got here late this season.
Less windy- less boat traffic than last week.
Hazy and calm.  Water surface relatively still.  All my readings are with "bare eyes".  Chop on surface can affect readings by 2-4'.
Ideal conditions for secchi reading-surface calm- bright and sunny day.
Overcast but very calm. No boat traffic.
Pleasantly warm. Sunny. Very light chop on the water. A great day to be on the lake.
Cool- windy. Boat traffic was heavy on the fourth. Secchi readings low. Temperature is unseasonable.
This reading seems more typical than last reading.
Windy- lots of boats- surface is very choppy
Surface ripples- but relatively calm. Little boat traffic.
Pair of loons produced one chick.
Beautiful day- but windy- saw 1 eagle- 2 loons with 1 chick- 1 duck with 11 ducklings.
Windy- mostly sunny- Don Bahr's first day as volunteer.
Some boat traffic- slight chop- Don Neumann's last day as a volunteer.
Early morning thunderstorm.  Partly cloudy with light chop.
Clear with slight chop + light traffic at time of test.
Saw loon family- sky clear with calm water in east bay- west bay light chop.
Clear + calm- beautiful day- saw 1 eagle + loon family.
Cool + clear. A tough of fall in the air.
Adult loons are gone- only young remain.
Partly cloudy- light traffic- cool and calm- and loon nesting on island.
Cloudy- windy- loon hatched two young- and saw mallard with nine young.
Cloudy- light breeze- and medium traffic.
Partly cloudy- wind and chop- and light traffic.
Clear- light breeze- and I saw an eagle.
Partly cloudy- windy- heavy thunder storms last night.
Clear and calm- perfect day for testing.
Partly cloudy- cold- breezy with chop.
Breeze with chop and mostly overcast with clear area over the lake.
Sunny with light breeze.  Loon nesting on island.  Saw 8 green heads.
Calm- partly cloudy.  Loon hatched.  1 chick.
Clear and sunny with light breeze.
Partly cloudy.  Heavy traffic.  Chop on surface.
Partly cloudy.  Light breeze with chop.
Partly cloudy.  Lake smells from algae.  Heavy traffic.
Partly coudy.  Windy.  Algae odor on lake.
Clear- windy East Basin - less wind West Basin.
training session with Jay Van Thiele. Kurt Klebe training also. calm  Kurt + Amy training on O2 + PH meters with Jay Van Thiele.  Calm- clear day. saw 3 loons- 1 crane and 2 eagles.  PH 8.5
Kurt + Amy Klebe  windy- partly cloudy  PH 8.6
Calm- cloudy day. 67 degrees. Saw an eagle and several fish jumping.
Cloudy- light wind- 68 degrees. Saw 3 loons
Calm water- blue sky. Air temp 70 Saw 2 adult loons- 2 baby loons and 1 eagle
Saw 1 eagle- 1 ospray and 3 loons (2 adults- 1 baby). Clear sunny day.
Saw 1 eagle- 2 adult loons- 1 baby loon- 1 ospray- 5 lake gulls- 7 ducks.  Clear and sunny.
Saw 2 adult loons- 1 baby loon- 1 lake gull- 1 osprey
Saw 2 adult loons- 1 juvenile loon- 1 eagle- 2 lake gulls- 3 fawns
Saw 1 eagle- 1 adult loon and 1 lake gull.
Saw 2 adult loons- 2 baby loons- 1 bald eagle- 1 heron and 2 mallard ducks.
saw 2 adult loons- 2 adolescent loons- 1 eagle- 1 osprey- 2 lake gulls.
saw 2 adult loons-1 loon chick- 6 geese
Smoky haze- possibly from Canadian wildfires  1 loon seen
